<h1>Problem 2293 - Amateurs Geometry Olympiad 3, P2 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(ABCD\) be a parallelogram and \(E\) a point on \(AD\) such that \(\angle ABE = \angle DBC\). Let \(O_A\) and \(O_C\) be the circumcenters of \(\triangle ABE\) and \(\triangle DBC\) respectively. Lines \(AO_C\) and \(CO_A\) meet at \(K\).</p>
<p>Prove that \(DC \perp BK\).</p>
